[[File:Nissan_Leaf_&_Chevy_Volt_charging_trimmed.jpg|thumb]]纯电动汽车（左），和[[雪佛兰沃蓝达|雪佛兰沃蓝达]](Chevy Volt)混合动力汽车（右）是世界上销量最好的可以在高速公路上行驶的充电式电动汽车。]]
'''充电式电动车辆'''（{{lang-en|plug-in electric vehicles}}, 缩写: PEVs）是一种可以通过外界电源（比如墙上插座）充电的[[机动车|机动车]]。车载的[[蓄电池|蓄电池]]提供车辆运行所需的全部或部分动力。充电式电动车辆是电动车的一种，其中包括[[纯电动车|纯电动车]]（all-electric or battery electric vehicles, BEVs）、 [[插电式混合动力汽车|充电式混合动力车辆]]（plug-in hybrid vehicles, PHEVs）、 经过改良的混合动力汽车或传统[[内燃机|内燃机]]车<ref name=PEVs>{{cite book|title=Plug-In Electric Vehicles: What Role for Washington?|editor=[[David_B._Sandalow|David B. Sandalow]]|year=2009|publisher=[[The_Brookings_Institution|The Brookings Institution]]|isbn=978-0-8157-0305-1|edition=1st.|url=http://www.brookings.edu/press/Books/2009/pluginelectricvehicles.aspx|pages=2–5|access-date=2013-07-04|archive-date=2019-03-28|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190328104012/https://www.brookings.edu/press/Books/2009/pluginelectricvehicles.aspx/|dead-url=no}} ''See definition on pp. 2.''</ref><ref name=CSE>{{cite web|url=http://energycenter.org/index.php/technical-assistance/transportation/electric-vehicles|title=Plug-in Electric Vehicles (PEVs)|publisher=Center for Sustainable Energy, California|accessdate=2010-03-31|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100620210051/http://energycenter.org/index.php/technical-assistance/transportation/electric-vehicles|archive-date=2010-06-20|dead-url=yes}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.duke-energy.com/plugin/pev-faqs.asp |title=PEV Frequently Asked Questions |publisher=[[Duke_Energy|Duke Energy]] |accessdate=2010-12-24 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120327101552/http://www.duke-energy.com/plugin/pev-faqs.asp |archivedate=2012-03-27 }}</ref>。

相比于传统内燃机车， [[插电式混合动力汽车|充电式混合动力车辆]]有很多好处。它们的运行和保养的成本比较低、可以减少当地的[[空气污染|空气污染]]、减少对[[石油|石油]]的依赖、并且有可能减少[[温室气体|温室气体]]的排放（取决于燃料和用来给蓄电池充电的发电技术）。 [[插电式混合动力汽车|充电式混合动力车辆]]只有运行在全电动模式下才有这些好处。虽然有这些好处，由于一些使用要面对的障碍和限制， [[插电式混合动力汽车|充电式混合动力车辆]]的市场渗透率比预想的要慢。截止至2013年，因为其[[锂离子电池|锂离子电池]]组的额外成本，充电式电动车辆比传统车辆或混合动力车辆要贵很多。其他影响采用电动车辆的因素包括公共或者私有充电基础建设的缺乏、（对于纯电动汽车来说，由于技术限制）司机对于到达目的地前耗尽电池的担心。 [[插电式混合动力汽车|充电式混合动力车辆]]可以消除司机对[[纯电动车|纯电动车]]辆的这种担心，因为内燃机可以当作备用动力，这样使得充电式混合动力车辆可以提供和传统车辆相当的里程数。

一些国家和政府制定了税收抵免、补贴、和其他鼓励机制（具体政策取决于电池大小和全电模式下的里程数）用来促进在大众市场引进和使用充电式电动车辆。“充电式电动车辆”（plug-in electric drive vehicle）这个词被正式的用在美国联邦立法里关于消费者的鼓励机制部分<ref name=IRS2009>{{cite web|url=http://www.irs.gov/irb/2009-48_IRB/ar09.html|title=Notice 2009-89: New Qualified Plug-in Electric Drive Motor Vehicle Credit|publisher=[[Internal_Revenue_Service|Internal Revenue Service]]|date=2009-11-30|accessdate=2010-04-01|archive-date=2010-09-28|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100928210245/http://www.irs.gov/irb/2009-48_IRB/ar09.html|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name=IRS0409>{{cite web|url=http://www.energy.gov/taxbreaks.htm|title=Consumer Energy Tax Incentives: Plug-In Hybrid Conversion Kits|publisher=[[U.S._Department_of_Energy|U.S. Department of Energy]]|accessdate=2010-04-01|archive-date=2010-04-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100403070431/http://www.energy.gov/taxbreaks.htm|dead-url=no}}</ref>。在中国，充电式电动车辆被叫做新能源车辆（new energy vehicles, NEVs），奖励机制只对购买[[纯电动车|纯电动车]]辆或充电式混合动力车辆有效<ref name=NEVs>{{cite web|url=http://siteresources.worldbank.org/EXTNEWSCHINESE/Resources/3196537-1202098669693/EV_Report_en.pdf|title=The China New Energy Vehicles Program - Challenges and Opportunities|author=PRTM Management Consultants, Inc|publisher=[[World_Bank|World Bank]]|date=April 2011|accessdate=2013-04-22|archive-date=2012-06-18|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120618074936/http://siteresources.worldbank.org/EXTNEWSCHINESE/Resources/3196537-1202098669693/EV_Report_en.pdf|dead-url=no}} ''See Acronyms and Key Terms, pp. v''</ref>。

目前世界上大多数充电式电动车辆是慢速、短程的邻里电动汽车。在2011年，派克研究公司（Pike Research）估计世界上大概有479,000量邻里电动汽车在路上行驶<ref name=NEVsales>{{cite web|url=http://www.autoobserver.com/2011/06/neighborhood-electric-vehicle-sales-to-climb.html|title=Neighborhood Electric Vehicle Sales To Climb|author=Danny King|publisher=[[Edmunds.com|Edmunds.com]] Auto Observer|date=2011-06-20|accessdate=2012-02-05|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120527110345/http://www.autoobserver.com/2011/06/neighborhood-electric-vehicle-sales-to-climb.html|archive-date=2012-05-27|dead-url=yes}}</ref>。最高销量的邻里电动汽车是GEM系列（Global Electric Motorcars）汽车，从1998年到2013年4月已经在全世界卖出了46,000台<ref name=GEMsales>{{cite web|url=http://finance.yahoo.com/news/ge-capital-finance-commercial-purchases-120000867.html|title=GE Capital to Finance Commercial Purchases of Global Electric Motorcars (GEM®)|publisher=[[Yahoo!_Finance|Yahoo! Finance]]|date=2013-05-02|accessdate=2013-05-03|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130727210829/http://finance.yahoo.com/news/ge-capital-finance-commercial-purchases-120000867.html|archivedate=2013-07-27}}</ref>。从2007年开始截止到2013年3月，全世界已经卖出了大概200,000辆可以在高速公路上行驶的充电式电动轿车和超过10,000辆电动通用面包车。全球销量增长从2007年到2010年总共的11,768辆<ref name=PEVs2007_10>{{cite news|url=http://www.ft.com/intl/cms/s/0/306347f4-cf32-11e1-bfd9-00144feabdc0.html#axzz2B1GDOwsd|title=Electric cars struggle to build momentum|author=John Reed|work=[[Financial_Times|Financial Times]]|date=2012-07-20|accessdate=2013-02-17}} ''See the infograph [http://im.ft-static.com/content/images/3458b5c6-d29b-11e1-abe7-00144feabdc0.img?width=913&height=904&title=&desc=Electric%20cars%20graphic Electric car sales lack spark] {{Wayback|url=http://im.ft-static.com/content/images/3458b5c6-d29b-11e1-abe7-00144feabdc0.img?width=913&height=904&title=&desc=Electric%20cars%20graphic |date=20130618175822 }} for yearly sales between 2007 and 2010''.</ref>到2011年的40,000辆<ref name=PEV40K2011>{{cite news|url=http://www.forbes.com/sites/justingerdes/2012/05/11/the-global-electric-vehicle-movement-best-practices-from-16-cities/|title=The Global Electric Vehicle Movement: Best Practices From 16 Cities|author=Justin Gerdes|work=[[Forbes|Forbes]]|date=2012-05-11|accessdate=2013-02-17|archive-date=2013-03-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130303151837/http://www.forbes.com/sites/justingerdes/2012/05/11/the-global-electric-vehicle-movement-best-practices-from-16-cities/|dead-url=no}}</ref>一年，再到2012年的119,300辆<ref name=PEV120K2012>{{cite news|url=http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-03-20/in-ghosn-we-trust-tested-as-nissan-electric-push-falters.html|title=In Ghosn We Trust Tested as Nissan Electric Push Falters|author=Ma Jie and Yuki Hagiwara|work=[[Bloomberg_L.P.|Bloomberg L.P.]]|date=2013-03-20|accessdate=2013-03-20|archive-date=2013-03-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130322181252/http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-03-20/in-ghosn-we-trust-tested-as-nissan-electric-push-falters.html|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name=PEV120K2012_2>{{cite news|url=http://www.nytimes.com/2013/02/10/world/europe/dutch-put-electric-cars-to-the-test.html|title=Plugging In, Dutch Put Electric Cars to the Test|author=Elisabeth Rosenthal|newspaper=[[The_New_York_Times|The New York Times]]|date=2013-02-09|accessdate=2013-02-11|archive-date=2013-02-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130211001247/http://www.nytimes.com/2013/02/10/world/europe/dutch-put-electric-cars-to-the-test.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。在充电式电动汽车销量方面，美国是世界的领先者，占有46%的世界销量，随后的是日本和欧洲，分别占有世界23%的销量<ref name=Top2012>{{cite news|url=http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-03-12/gm-s-chevy-volt-outsold-nissan-leaf-last-year-bnef-says.html|title=GM’s Chevy Volt Outsold Nissan Leaf Last Year, BNEF Says|author=Siddharth Philip|work=[[Bloomberg_L.P.|Bloomberg L.P.]]|date=2013-03-12|accessdate=2013-03-30|archive-date=2013-03-15|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130315031423/http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-03-12/gm-s-chevy-volt-outsold-nissan-leaf-last-year-bnef-says.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。如果以不同的类别来看，美国是2012年充电式混合动力汽车销量的领先者，占有70%的世界销量。而日本以占有28%的世界销量成为纯电动汽车销量的领先者，紧随其后的是美国，占有26%的世界销量<ref name=Outook2013>{{cite web |url=http://www.iea.org/publications/globalevoutlook_2013.pdf |title=Global EV Outlook 2013 - Understanding the Electric Vehicle Landscape to 2020 |author=[[International_Energy_Agency|International Energy Agency]], Clean Energy Ministerial, and Electric Vehicles Initiative |publisher=International Energy Agency |date=April 2013 |accessdate=2013-04-20 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130423003013/http://www.iea.org/publications/globalevoutlook_2013.pdf |archivedate=2013-04-23 }} ''See pp. 4, 6-8, and 11-12''.</ref>。

