===充电式电动车辆===
充电式电动车辆是任何可以由[[输电网络|电网]]充电的机动车。车载[[蓄电池|电池]]提供车辆运行所需的全部或部分动力<ref name=PEVs/><ref name=CSE/>。充电式电动车辆有时也被称为电网支持车辆（grid-enabled vehicles, GEV）<ref name=CSE/>或者电动可充电车辆（electrically chargeable vehicles）<ref name=ACEA1>{{cite web|url=http://www.acea.be/index.php/news/news_detail/electric_vehicles_turning_buzz_into_reality/|title=Electric Vehicles: Turning Buzz into Reality|publisher=[[European_Automobile_Manufacturers_Association|European Automobile Manufacturers Association]]|date=2010-02-09|accessdate=2010-04-23|archive-date=2010-03-29|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100329032149/http://www.acea.be/index.php/news/news_detail/electric_vehicles_turning_buzz_into_reality/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

充电式电动车辆是电动车辆的其中一种，包括了[[纯电动车|纯电动车辆]]（battery electric vehicles, BEVs）、[[插电式混合动力汽车|充电式混合动力车辆]]（plug-in hybrid vehicles, PHEVs）、经过改良的混合动力车辆（hybrid electric vehicles, HEVs）或[[内燃机|内燃机]]车辆（internal combustion engine vehicles）<ref name=PEVs/><ref name=CSE/>。虽然传统的混合动力车辆带有可以通过内燃机和[[再生制动|再生制动]]充电的电池，它们不能通过外界电源充电，所以不属于充电式电动车辆。<ref name=PEVs/><ref name=CSE/>

“充电式电动车辆”（plug-in electric drive vehicle）这个词被用在美国联邦立法里去称呼可以接受税收抵免的车辆类型（根据车辆的电池大小和纯电模式下的里程）<ref name=IRS2009/><ref name=IRS0409/>。在一些欧洲国家，特别是法国，“可充电车辆”（electrically chargeable veicle）是正式用来称呼可以接受这些鼓励机制的车辆类型<ref name=ACEA2>{{cite web|url=http://www.acea.be/index.php/news/news_detail/an_increasing_number_of_member_states_levy_co2_based_taxation_or_incentivis/|title=An Increasing Number of Member States Levy CO2-Based Taxation or Incentivise Electric Vehicles|publisher=[[European_Automobile_Manufacturers_Association|European Automobile Manufacturers Association]]|date=2010-04-21|accessdate=2010-04-23|archive-date=2010-04-25|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100425010516/http://www.acea.be/index.php/news/news_detail/an_increasing_number_of_member_states_levy_co2_based_taxation_or_incentivis|dead-url=yes}}</ref>。虽然“充电式电动车辆”这个词一般指[[汽车|汽车]]或者充电式汽车，它还包括其他类型的充电式车辆，包括[[速克达|速克达]]、[[摩托车|摩托车]]、邻里电动车或[[迷你车|迷你车]]、[[都市车|都市车]]、[[厢型车|面包车]]、轻型卡车或轻型商用车、[[公共汽车|公共汽车]]、[[载货汽车|货车]]、军用车辆<ref name=PEVTracker>{{cite web|url=http://www.pluginamerica.org/vehicles|title=Plug-in Vehicle Tracker: What's Coming, When|publisher=[[Plug_In_America|Plug In America]]|accessdate=2012-01-15|archive-date=2013-01-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130111054917/http://www.pluginamerica.org/vehicles|dead-url=yes}}</ref><ref name=NYT0404>{{cite news|url=http://wheels.blogs.nytimes.com/2013/04/04/a-new-electric-car-with-an-old-name/?ref=automobiles|title=A New Electric Car With an Old Name|author=Paul Stenquist|work=[[The_New_York_Times|The New York Times]]|date=2013-04-01|accessdate=2013-04-04|archive-date=2013-04-28|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130428014629/http://wheels.blogs.nytimes.com/2013/04/04/a-new-electric-car-with-an-old-name/?ref=automobiles|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

===纯电动车辆===
{{Main|纯电动车}}
纯电动车辆只使用储存在可充电电池里的能量作为动力<ref name=CSE/><ref name=EERE_EV>{{cite web|url=http://www.afdc.energy.gov/afdc/vehicles/electric_basics_ev.html|title=All-Electric Vehicle Basics|publisher=Alternative Fuels & Advanced Vehicles Data Center, US DoE|accessdate=2010-12-29|archive-date=2010-10-23|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20101023080937/http://www.afdc.energy.gov/afdc/vehicles/electric_basics_ev.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。它们用[[电动机|电动机]]和电机控制器来替代内燃机提供动力<ref name=CSE/>。

当充电式混合动力车辆在[[消耗電量模式|消耗電量模式]]（charge-depleting mode）下运行时就相当于纯电动车辆，但当它的[[电量状态|电量]]达到最低限度的时候，它就耗尽了它纯电模式下的里程，并会转到保持电量模式（charge-sustaining mode）<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.spinnovation.com/sn/Reports/Driving_Plug-In_Hybrid_Electric_Vehicles_-_reports_from_US_drivers_of_PHEVs.pdf|title=Driving Plug-In Hybrid Electric Vehicles: Reports from U.S. Drivers of HEVs converted to PHEVs, circa 2006-07|publisher=Institute of Transportation Studies, [[University_of_California,_Davis|University of California, Davis]]|author=Kurani et al|date=2007-10-16|accessdate=2010-12-29|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100812140505/http://www.spinnovation.com/sn/Reports/Driving_Plug-In_Hybrid_Electric_Vehicles_-_reports_from_US_drivers_of_PHEVs.pdf|archive-date=2010-08-12|dead-url=yes}} ''See definitions in pp. 1-2''.</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://web.mit.edu/sloan-auto-lab/research/beforeh2/files/kromer_electric_powertrains.pdf|title=Electric Powertrains: Opportunities and Challenges in the U.S. Light-Duty Vehicle Fleet|author=Matthew A. Kromer and John B. Heywood|publisher=Sloan Automotive Laboratory, [[Massachusetts_Institute_of_Technology|Massachusetts Institute of Technology]]|date=May 2007|accessdate=2010-12-29|archive-date=2010-09-23|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100923001509/http://web.mit.edu/sloan-auto-lab/research/beforeh2/files/kromer_electric_powertrains.pdf|dead-url=no}} ''See definitions in pp. 30-31''.</ref>。

===充电式混合动力车辆===
{{Main|插电式混合动力汽车}}
充电式混合动力车辆（或插电式混合动力车辆）是一种可以通过外界电源充电的混合动力车型<ref name=CSE/><ref name=EERE_PHEV>{{cite web|url=http://www.afdc.energy.gov/afdc/vehicles/electric_basics_phev.html|title=Plug-in Hybrid Electric Vehicle Basics|publisher=Alternative Fuels & Advanced Vehicles Data Center, US DoE|accessdate=2010-12-29|archive-date=2011-02-21|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110221123814/http://www.afdc.energy.gov/afdc/vehicles/electric_basics_phev.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。充电式混合动力车型包含了传统混合动力车型和纯电动车型的特点：使用了汽油发动机和电动机来提供动力，但是它有更大的可充电的电池组，这样使得它可以在纯电动模式下运行更久<ref name=EERE_PHEV/><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ceage.vt.edu/phev|title=Plug-In Hybrid Electric Vehicle (PHEV)|publisher=Center for Energy and the Global Environment, [[Virginia_Tech|Virginia Tech]]|accessdate=2010-12-29|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110720110541/http://www.ceage.vt.edu/phev|archivedate=2011-07-20}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hybridcars.com/plug-in-hybrid-cars|title=What Is A Plug-in Hybrid Car?|publisher=HybridCars.com|accessdate=2010-12-29|archive-date=2011-05-04|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110504025512/http://www.hybridcars.com/plug-in-hybrid-cars|dead-url=no}}</ref>。
